Interface LazyAXML<S extends LazyAXML<S,T>,T>

    public interface LazyAXML<S extends LazyAXML<S,T>,T>
extends AXMLBase<S,T>
    Basic interface for AXML data with lazy child components, which are accessed as streams.

      • build

        AXMLBase.Builder<S> build(java.util.function.Consumer<AXMLBase.Publisher<? super T>> generator)
        Build a new instance of this class by calculating child components lazily. The generator's lambda body ... in data.build((Publisher<T> publisher) -> ... ) to generate the enclosed children, runs when their values are required.
        Parameters:
        generator - lazy generator of the contents
        Returns:
        A builder for returned new instance.

        void forEach(AXMLBase.Publisher<? super T> action)

      • forEachBuild

        AXMLBase.Builder<S> forEachBuild(java.util.function.BiConsumer<T,AXMLBase.Publisher<? super T>> mapper)
        Build a new instance of this class whose contents are calculated lazily. This method represents an optimized combination of build and forEach. I.e., data.forEachBuild((T document, Publisher<T> publisher) -> ... ) is the same as data.build((Publisher<T> publisher) -> data.forEach((T document) -> ... )) .
